{
  "texts": [
    "We do this so that the problem description is as common as possible across different algorithms.",
    "Scale-free graphs have a power law probability distribution for the node degree, d, of the form P(d) ∝ d - where is typically between 2 and 3.",
    "The resulting network has a small number of nodes with many tens or more of neighbours which are known as hubs.",
    "Biological networks such as gene regulation or metabolic networks are often scale-free, for example."
  ]
}